parameters:
The exploration of this large hole has hardly progressed. There
are troublesome monsters placed to defend it...

It's like looking at the gates of hell. I wonder how a hole like
this could have been created...

Are we going down there? Seriously...? I was scared and ran
back...

I might be able to handle a little bit of magic, but I'm not that
skilled... Besides, um... I'm a little scared, to be honest.

There's something strange about this place. It's like something
is off, like it doesn't belong in this world...
\SE[2]This is the Trial of the Earth...!\SE[59]Ruins... I see.

\SE[88]No... What is this ruins!? \SE[17]Wasn't this supposed to
be my place in order...?

\SE[5]Until just a little while ago, there were normal trials,
right? \SE[3]I wonder if something happened, like an accident...?

\SE[2]It seems like we still don't understand the area around
here. \SE[58]But still, what a huge hole... I wonder what's at
the bottom...

\SE[4]Hey... It's amazing, isn't it...? \SE[3]Even with Lunaroa's
magic, it wouldn't have become this bad...

\SE[2]Earth Spirit... I wonder what happened. \SE[3]If it's
alive, I would like to hear its story...

\SE[14]That's right... 'Earth Spirit'...!! \SE[17]I also want to
be able to 'shine' like everyone else...!! I want to do it...!!
\SE[10]Why... Why...? \SE[35]Why am I being treated like this...?

\SE[74]Well... Let's explore as requested. \SE[3]There's also a
possibility of finding the Spirit....

\SE[6]Y-Yes...! \SE[0]There is still hope...! Don't give up,
Vita...!

\SE[15]I'm counting on you, Earth Spirit... \SE[16]Because I
believe in you...!!

The 'Trial of the Earth' has been added to the teleportation
crystal!

I wonder what's at the bottom of the hole...? For some reason, I
couldn't start a fire.

If you're planning to go, be careful because you won't be able to
rest by a campfire.

There should have been an altar here dedicated to the earth
spirits... And yet suddenly there's such a huge hole...

It is possible for holes to form due to a decrease in
groundwater, but there are no underground water veins in this
area. Hmmm...
